The paper deals with the decomposition of arrangements of hyperplanes and its application to point location, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses the VC-dimension and primal shatter dimension, which are concepts in computational learning theory (cs.LG) and combinatorics (cs.DM). The analysis of the algorithms involves complexity analysis and tradeoffs, which are topics in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper is published in arXiv, which is a repository for computer science papers (cs.CC).
